# Engineering process (Cursor)

## Always load

`read_file` **`docs/guides/ENGINEERING_PROCESS.md`** before adding or restructuring:

- PRDs (`docs/prd/`)
- UXS (`docs/uxs/`)
- RFCs (`docs/rfc/`)
- ADRs (`docs/adr/`)
- Core architecture narrative (`docs/architecture/`)

## Condensed chain (full detail in the guide)

| Doc | Role |
| --- | --- |
| **PRD** | What and why (product); success criteria |
| **UXS** | UX and visual contract when UI changes |
| **RFC** | **How** — full technical design, trade-offs, migration |
| **ADR** | **Law** — brief **Accepted** decisions **taken from** the RFC |

Do **not** put the whole RFC design into an ADR. Do **not** use **Accepted** on RFC headers (RFC uses **Draft** / **Completed**).

## Checklist on exit

- Correct **status vocabulary** for doc type (see `documentation.mdc`).
- New RFC/ADR: **`docs/rfc/index.md`** / **`docs/adr/index.md`** updated when applicable.
- **`make docs`** + **`make lint-markdown`** after substantive markdown edits.
